    <p>Some may shun wrig­gly worms, but these crea­tures play a crit­i­cal role both on land and in the ocean. Marine flat­worms, with their swirling ‘gowns’, are also the flam­boy­ant fla­menco dancers of the sea. The Straits Times un­cov­ers why worms can be slimy, yet sub­lime.</p>


